Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Cells were grown up to 150 mm plates with the appropriate media.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Cells were crosslinked, flash frozen, and sent to Active Motif. According to Active Motif protocol, cells were lysed, sonicated, and then DNA-protein complexes were isolated with antibodies. Samples were reverse-crosslinked and DNA was purified., Illumina libraries were prepared by Active Motif using standard consecutive enzymatic steps of end-polishing, dA-addition, and adaptor ligation. After 15 cycles of PCR amplification, the resulting DNA libraries were quantified and sequenced on Illumina NextSeq 500.
Sample_data_processing: FASTQ sequences were adapter and quality trimmed using TrimGalore., Phred scores were calculated per sample and used during hg19 alignment with bwa samse., Picard tools was used to remove duplicate reads., Fragment sizes were estimated using MaSC and these values were used as input into MACS2 for narrow peak calling., Peaks were called significant using a q-value cut off of 0.05 and results were returned in units of signal per million reads.

Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Cells were grown in 150 mm cell culture plates with appropriate media until ~70-80%.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: For ChIP-Seq, cells were crosslinked, flash frozen, and sent to Active Motif. According to Active Motif protocol, cells were lysed, sonicated, and then DNA-protein complexes were isolated with antibodies. Samples were reverse-crosslinked and DNA was purified. For ATAC-Seq, whole cells were frozen and sent to Active Motif for thawing and transposition., Illumina libraries were prepared by Active Motif using standard consecutive enzymatic steps of end-polishing, dA-addition, and adaptor ligation. After 15 cycles of PCR amplification, the resulting DNA libraries were quantified and sequenced by Jefferson Cancer Genomics Laboratory at the Kimmel Cancer Center using the NexSeq 500.
Sample_data_processing: FASTQ sequences were adapter and quality trimmed using TrimGalore., Phred scores were calculated per sample and used during hg19 alignment with bwa samse., Picard tools v.2.17.9-SNAPSHOT was used to remove duplicate reads., Fragment sizes were estimated using MaSC and these values were used as input into MACS2 for broad peak calling., Peaks were called significant using a q-value cut off of 0.05 and results were returned in units of signal per million reads.

According to Active Motif protocol, cells were lysed, sonicated, and then DNA-protein complexes were isolated with antibodies. Samples were reverse-crosslinked and DNA was purified. For ATAC-Seq, whole cells were frozen and sent to Active Motif for thawing and transposition., Illumina libraries were prepared by Active Motif using standard consecutive enzymatic steps of end-polishing, dA-addition, and adaptor ligation. After 15 cycles of PCR amplification, the resulting DNA libraries were quantified and sequenced by Jefferson Cancer Genomics Laboratory at the Kimmel Cancer Center using the NexSeq 500.
Sample_data_processing: FASTQ sequences were adapter and quality trimmed using TrimGalore., Phred scores were calculated per sample and used during hg19 alignment with bwa samse., Picard tools v.2.17.9-SNAPSHOT was used to remove duplicate reads., Fragment sizes were estimated using MaSC and these values were used as input into MACS2 for broad peak calling., Peaks were called significant using a q-value cut off of 0.05 and results were returned in units of signal per million reads.
